RIYADH: Saudi Minister of Environment, Water, and Agriculture Abdul Rahman Al-Fadli recently inaugurated an exhibition on Kyrgyz culture being staged in Riyadhâ€™s Digital City.
Organized by the ministry in cooperation with the Kyrgyzstan Embassy, the opening was attended by the Kyrgyz Minister of Culture, Information, Sports and Youth Policies Azamat Zhamankulov, Deputy Minister of Agriculture Azamat Mukachev, Acting Minister of Investment Nuradil Bayasov, Ambassador to Saudi Arabia Ulukbek Maripov, and other senior officials and business figures from both countries.
The four-day exhibition aims to develop bilateral ties through cultural awareness of Kyrgyzstan, displaying Kyrgyz products to Saudi society, as well as introducing tourist destinations in the central Asian country.
More than 25 exhibitors representing various businesses and industrial companies participated in the exhibition activities.
Meanwhile, a forum for businesspeople and the Chamber of Commerce and Industry will be held on the sidelines of the exhibition on Feb. 27 and will include workshops and discussion sessions on issues affecting the business community. 